narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I have a better understanding of the process of translation and more confidence in my own translations.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: We covered a lot of extremely interesting material in this course. I did feel like the amount of work for each class varied considerably week by week, and some weeks we had more to cover than we were able to get through, but this was because the material was all engaging.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I think this course helps one to understand some of the issues of the translation, and reception more generally, of Greek and Roman texts, and it was an enjoyable course.
